article.headline: Texas State 67, Northwestern St. 64
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. (AP) -- Roosevelt Brown scored 22 points, including 6-of-7 from the free throw line, and Josh Naylor added 20 as Texas State beat Northwestern State 67-64 Saturday. The victory left Texas State (11-7, 6-1) in first place in the Southland Conference, breaking a three-way tie with Northwestern (8-10, 5-2) and Southeastern Louisiana. Southeastern did not play Saturday. Northwestern led by 10 points (32-22) at the half after holding Texas State to 25 percent shooting from the field. The Bobcats rallied in the second half, taking the lead for the first time with less than three minutes to play on a 3-point basket by Naylor to make it 54-51. Texas State went up by six points before the Demons cut the lead to three. Northwestern failed to tie the game when two 3-pointers fell short in the closing minute. Zach Allison scored 11 points for Texas State. Jermaine Wallace led Northwestern with 18 points and 10 rebounds. Clifton Lee scored 15, Byron Allen added nine points and nine rebounds.
